I've been wanting to try some TN style parottas here in Gachibowli and found out about this restaurant nearby DLF.¬† It is somewhat a smaller place with not much of an ambiance. You go in there for quick bite of munchy South Indian tiffin items like Idly, Dosa and vada.¬†
I ordered for the parotta kuruma and I have to say, coming from Chennai, the parotta could have been a lot better. It was okayish and I felt it was reheated and not made fresh. The kuruma too was somewhat bland in taste and could have been better.
Will be staying here in Hyderabad for some more weeks and will probably try out their other dishes when I feel a need to have something TN style.

It was opened recently and we went there to try some southindian cuisines and this restaurant didn't disappoint us at all.Tried here idli,vada,masala dosa and Pongal..They all were very tasty .Ambience was ok ok.Must visit if u r nearby to DLF.
I ordered so many times from here idli sambar is so tasty chutney is not good and food packing is really good it was too hot and delivery was very quickly
